			<node ID="ID_1510648679" TEXT="A lot of my ideas about Machine Learning come from Quantum Mechanical Perturbation Theory. To provide some context we need to step back and understand that the familiar techniques of Machine Learning like Spectral Clustering are in fact nearly identical to Quantum Mechanical Spectroscopy. As usual this will take several blogs. Here I give&#8230;" />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_186861369" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cluster_analysis" TEXT="Cluster analysis - Wikipedia">
			<node ID="ID_1712401013" TEXT="Cluster analysis or clustering is the task of grouping a set of objects in such a way that objects in the same group (called a cluster) are more similar (in some sense) to each other than to those in other groups (clusters).It is a main task of exploratory data mining and a common technique for statistical data analysis used in many fields including machine learning pattern recognition " />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_1598918696" LINK="https://web.stanford.edu/class/cs345a/slides/12-clustering.pdf" TEXT="Clustering Algorithms - Stanford University">
