			<node ID="ID_88460528" TEXT="A Data Vizzer will probably be very upset if you call their work an Infographic. Confused? As someone who makes a lot of infographics and now has a data visualization under her belt let me explain the difference! Data Visualizations Are Interactive . First and foremost Data Visualizations are almost always" />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_360310404" LINK="https://www.dictionary.com/browse/visualization" TEXT="Visualization | Definition of Visualization at Dictionary.com">
			<node ID="ID_1816261862" TEXT="Visualization definition to recall or form mental images or pictures. See more." />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_1381102547" LINK="https://medium.com/multiple-views-visualization-research-explained/uncertainty-visualization-explained-67e7a73f031b" TEXT="Uncertainty + Visualization Explained &#8211; Multiple Views ">
			<node ID="ID_19587714" TEXT="TLDR: The first in a series summarizing what we know about visualizing uncertainty in data. This post covers what we mean by &#8220;uncertainty&#8221; in visualization and considers a few subtle yet&#8230;" />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_943715328" LINK="https://readwrite.com/2011/01/07/difference-between-datavisualization-infographics/" TEXT="3 Views on the Difference Between a Data Visualization and ">
			<node ID="ID_1237072107" TEXT="3 Views on the Difference Between a Data Visualization and an Infographic.  animated or interactive. So I think the difference is more about the objective.  usually by means of well-known " />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_633974409" LINK="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_visualization" TEXT="Data visualization - Wikipedia">
			<node ID="ID_125378467" TEXT="Data visualization is viewed by many disciplines as a modern equivalent of visual communication.It involves the creation and study of the visual representation of data.. To communicate information clearly and efficiently data visualization uses statistical graphics plots information graphics and other tools. Numerical data may be encoded using dots lines or bars to visually communicate a " />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_334512453" LINK="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/visualization" TEXT="Visualization | Definition of Visualization by Merriam-Webster">
			<node ID="ID_192114111" TEXT="Visualization definition is - formation of mental visual images. 3: the process of making an internal organ or part visible by the introduction (as by swallowing) of a radiopaque substance followed by radiography" />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_1162035154" LINK="https://rpsychologist.com/d3/NHST/" TEXT="Understanding Statistical Power and Significance Testing ">
